direction.raw_text: Emergency.
direction.name: direction

direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: No!   Don't say that!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: This is Emergency Services. Not dial-a-joke. (CONTINUED)
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: . CONTINUED: CLICK. The LINE GOES DEAD. Chris climbs up beside him. He FIRES several BLASTS at the approaching spiders.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: What happened?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: They didn't believe me!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: What a shock!     Try again! The spiders are closing in as Harlan re-dials.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Emergency.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: There was a massive explosion! Everybody's dead!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Sir, your number has been flagged as a source of a crank call. I'm afraid I must terminate this conversation. CLICK.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: She hung up on me!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Climb! Chris FIRES the SHOTGUN.       The spiders are closing in. INT. MALL - NIGHT Sam gazes up at the skylight. She can see the silhouette of Chris and Harlan climbing the antenna. Pursued by spiders.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Oh my God... Ashley screams in horror nearby.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: They're inside! (CONTINUED)
direction.name: direction

direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Over here! He faces off against more spiders coming through the Home and Garden store. EXT. MALL - ROOF - ANTENNA - NIGHT Harlan is at the top. Chris is a bit lower. The spiders are still coming. Chris SHOOTS at them. His GUN RUNS DRY. He flips it around and butt-strokes an approaching arac. A spider fires a web at Harlan.       Nails the poor guy.   And drags him off the antenna. Harlan falls off the antenna, back toward the spiders. Chris reaches out and grabs him. Holding Harlan's hand.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I've got you! Harlan makes eye-contact with Chris.       They're both about to be killed unless...
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Defend the human race!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: No! Harlan jerks away from Chris's hand. He cannonballs down into the horde of spiders. Splattering several of the beasts along with himself. Chris throws the useless shotgun at an approaching arac and climbs even higher. He pulls out his machete and begins hacking at the guide-wires that hold the antenna upright. The spiders close in. Chris slices one wire. The antenna quivers. Chris slices another wire. The antenna shakes. INT. MALL - NIGHT Deputy Pete is standing with Sam and the kids when he's jerked off his feet and hauled into the maw of an arachnid. (CONTINUED)
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: . CONTINUED:
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Ashley!   Mike! She sees Mike and Ashley avoid an arac by taking refuge inside the tunnels of the jungle gym. Sam FIRES the GUNS like Annie Oakley, putting spiders down left and right, trying to reach her kids. Floyd the barber confronts a spider with his chain-saw.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Having a bad hair day?! The spider charges.     Floyd slices its legs off.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: How about a little off the top! He slices another arac. EXT. MALL - ROOF - ANTENNA - NIGHT Chris dodges a spider's webline.       Several more come at him.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: You're going down! Chris cuts the last wire and hikes out over the skylight. The antenna keels over. Chris hangs tight as he drops toward the glass. INT. MALL - NIGHT Sam looks up to   see Chris come crashing down through the skylight on the   antenna. The antenna tilts in at a sixty degree angle.    Chris hangs off the end. Orb weavers ride their weblines   down to the floor of the mall. Mike peeks out from the top of the jungle gym. He sees a hundred spiders coming in on webs. Flooding out of the stores. The devil-spawned monsters are everywhere!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Arac attack! Chris leaps from the antenna to a nearby web. He slides down it like a pole, squashing the orb weaver at the bottom. Sam runs to his side. (CONTINUED)
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: . CONTINUED:
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Did you get help?!    Is anybody coming!?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: We're on our own! Sam tosses him a gun and they head toward the jungle gym. The waitress roller-skates away from the spiders. She slaloms clear of several spitters. But gets tackled by a jumper. INT. MALL - JUNGLE GYM Ashley and Mike are hiding.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I can't stay in here! Ashley starts to move out   of the tube. She discovers the end has been covered with   web. She pushes it. Something on the other side pushes   back. Ashley scrambles back. Mike is already moving.    The kids flee through the tubes to get away.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: What are they doing?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: They're trapping us like ants in a log! Once they have all the exits blocked, they'll come in through the last one! They see a way out, head for that exit, only to find a spider coming through it. Mike tosses one of his perfume grenades at the spider, covering their retreat. Another spider comes after them through one of the tubes. Mike chucks another perfume bottle. The spider cowers.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: We've gotta go! Ashley finds a hole that leads to the slide.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Here! She starts down with Mike close behind. A large spider looms at the end. Ashley tries to arrest her slide. But it's no use. At the last second Sam's boot kicks the arachnid clear.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: . INT. MALL - NIGHT Ashley and Mike pour out of the slide. Chris and Sam finish off the spider and then run with the kids. Emma runs parallel to them across the playground's sandbox. Only to be yanked under by a trapdoor spider. Hank sees this and goes after the spiders with all his tools. Getting revenge with a nail gun in each hand.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: It's tool time! Floyd is still going crazy, slicing spiders with his chain-saw, he lets out a victorious yell until a hungry spider descends on him from above and knocks him to the floor. Chris passes a clothing store displaying Levi 501s.    He stops for a moment to look at the jeans.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Chris! Chris continues on. All of the survivors meet in the middle of the mall and prepare for Custer's last stand. Spiders charge from all directions. Mike throws his perfume grenades. Sam and Chris SHOOT. Others use their make-shift weapons. Norman pulls out a joint and sparks it.    Mike sees this and gets an idea.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Where do you grow your weed?!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Dude, if I tell you, I have to kill you. Norman takes a hit on his reefer.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: They're going to kill us, you stoner! Norman sees the army of spiders closing in.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Over here! (CONTINUED)
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: . CONTINUED: Norman opens    an access door. Sam and the other survivors run over and    crowd through it. Norman shuts the door behind them.     The groups of pursuing spiders collide and begin ripping    each other to pieces in a feeding frenzy. INT. MALL - ACCESS STAIRS - NIGHT Norman leads the survivors down the tight hallway.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Where are you taking us?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: To Shangri-la. INT. MALL - BASEMENT POT ROOM - NIGHT Norman leads the survivors into a basement room full of pot paraphernalia. Hookahs. Weed growing in hydroponic units under battery powered lights. Psychedelic posters.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: You aren't going to arrest me for this are you?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Not today. The group can hear SPIDERS BASHING at the upstairs door.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Oh great! Now you've trapped us! Chris moves to the bottom of the stairs.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: We should be able to hold them off for a little while. Suddenly a loud BANGING ERUPTS on the wall behind them.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: They're coming through the wall! The group tightens up. Back to back. Ready for the end. Suddenly a human hand punches through the wall.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: What the hell? (CONTINUED)
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: . CONTINUED: Bret Hale rips through the drywall. Filthy but alive. Standing in a horizontal mine shaft. He sees Sam's gun pointed right at him.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I didn't touch her!     I swear! Sam looks at Ashley.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Don't waste your bullets. Wade embraces his son.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I thought you were a goner, boy! Chris steps to the opening for a closer look at the mine.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: We can get out this way!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Aren't the spiders in there?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Not until daylight. The BANGING on the upper door gets more INTENSE. Norman grabs a flashlight and a bunch of battery powered grow lights from his weed farm. He passes them out to the group. Chris takes the flashlight and leads the way into the mine shaft. Bret is shocked as the others follow him. The group uses the grow lights, and flashlights.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: You're going back in there?!       Are you all crazy!?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Come on, Bret!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: No way!   I'm not going! Bret is alone in the room as the upper DOOR IMPLODES and spiders flood downstairs. Bret dives through the opening.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: . INT. MINE TUNNEL - NIGHT Bret runs past Sam and Chris. Sam FIRES her SHOTGUN at the first spider that enters the tunnel. Her GUN CLICKS DRY. She un-holsters her PISTOLS and FIRES.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Cover me!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: What are you going to do?! Chris uses the machete to cleave into the tunnel's upper support beam. More spiders come into the tunnel. Sam FIRES desperately. Chris keeps on hacking.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Hurry! Sam's GUNS CLICK DRY. Spiders charge. Chris swings the machete hard. The ROOF COLLAPSES onto the attacking spiders. Chris and Sam leap back. Landing in a heap. Clouds of dust swirl around them. They are tangled up for an awkward beat. Their faces just inches from each other...
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Hold that thought. They manage to disengage and move on. INT. MINE TUNNEL - NIGHT Chris and Sam move toward the bobbing lights of the few remaining survivors.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: We're trapped again!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: At least they can't follow us.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Which way do we go?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I think we're in one of the old tunnels.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Can you get us out of here?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Don't worry, Sam. Chris takes point with the others following nervously.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: . INT. MINES - JUNCTION - NIGHT A boarded-up shaft entrance. Suddenly the WOOD SPLINTERS. Chris and the others bash through. They file into a slightly more open area with two branching tunnels. The place is stacked from floor to ceiling with barrels of toxic waste.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I don't believe it... Mike recognizes the BioHazard warning label he saw on the barrel in the drainage ditch.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I've seen one of these before!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: What are they?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Toxic waste.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Where did you see it, Mike?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: The creek where Joshua gets his spider food. There was one in the water. Chris starts toward the sloping tunnel.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: We can get out this way!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: No, we can't. (turns to Wade) Isn't that tunnel blocked off, Dad? Chris and the others look at Wade.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Uh... yeah... he's right.   We can't get out that way.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: You did this?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I knew you'd never sell... We're under my property so... (CONTINUED)
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: . CONTINUED:
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: You put all of us at risk.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I didn't have a choice! I was broke! They gave me a hundred grand! Sam punches him.     Knocking Wade to the ground.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I think our lives are worth a little more than that.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: We're wasting time. Chris heads toward the only exit available. The others follow. Wade staggers to his feet. Stumbling after them. INT. MINE TUNNEL - NIGHT Chris leads the group down a tunnel. They come across bits of vintage mining gear. A string of old light bulbs runs along the roof into both tunnels.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: One end of these lights should be connected to a generator. That'll be near the entrance. They continue down the tunnel.     Entering... INT. MINES - TARANTULA DEN - NIGHT A large cavern. Animal carcasses litter the ground. Some human remains. Dead pets. Dead ostriches.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: My birds! You see, Sam? I wasn't lying! That's what I can put on the insurance form... giant spiders!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Ewww... what's that smell? The others are reacting strongly. (CONTINUED)
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: . CONTINUED:
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Methane.   This cavern is full of gas.
direction.name: direction

direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: One spark and we're all dead. Norman swallows his glowing joint. Chris shines his flashlight on a pile of mummy bundles.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: That's what I was talking about, Chris. Presents from the male tarantula to the female.
direction.name: direction

Yellowed teeth sneer from a shattered skull. He's completely desiccated. Every ounce of liquid drained away. Mike hides his eyes.     Ashley comforts him.
direction.name: direction

direction.name: direction

direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Gladys, please... (to the others) Can anybody help her?! (CONTINUED)
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: . CONTINUED: Suddenly Ashley pushes her way forward.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Her breathing is shallow.       She's going into arrest. Ashley proceeds with CPR. Just like she saw on TV. Suddenly Gladys snaps out of it. Gasping for air.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: It's okay.    It's okay. Gladys starts to get a grip. Trying to focus on Chris. From this angle Chris look like he has a golden halo.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Am I... dead?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: You're okay.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I'm not in heaven?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: No...
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Gold! Gold!     Look!    It's everywhere!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Is it real? Chris checks it out.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Jesus... it's the mother lode... He was right. My dad was right... Chris helps Gladys to her feet.         They share an emotional look of recognition.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: So were you. (CONTINUED)
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: . CONTINUED: Wade chips away at the gold.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Get as much as you can! Bret looks at Ashley.
direction.name: direction

direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: You saved my life. Ashley smiles. Gladys leans over to Norman.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Have you got a smoke, kid?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: The man says this cavern is full of highly flammable methane gas. I smoke to get high, not to die.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Spiders! The group sees a cluster of normal-sized tarantulas scuttling out of the shadows.
direction.name: direction

direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I think you should stop.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Why?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: They don't have hair. They aren't fully grown tarantulas. Chris and Sam look over. (CONTINUED)
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: . CONTINUED:
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: They're giant babies! Norman freezes. He hears SOMETHING MOVING around in the dark. And then a spine chilling... GROWL. Chris reacts to the noise.    He can guess what's coming... The FEMALE TARANTULA steps out of the shadows. Consuela has grown to be as big as a Volkswagen MicroBus. By far the largest spider we've seen yet. Covered in hair. Massive eyes. Her two fangs are the size of machetes. Mike's eyes go wide at the sight of his old nemesis.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Consuela.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Consuela? The fur on Consuela's back seems to undulate. There is something weird there. A lot of weird things. In fact... her entire back is littered with hundreds of baby tarantulas. As Consuela advances, she flicks several dart-sized quills off her belly right into Norman. A dark stain spreads across the drug dealer's shirt.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Bummer... Consuela pierces Norman with her fangs, holding him tight. Babies flood of her back and onto the doper, chewing him to pieces like ravenous piranhas.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Go! The group flees toward the opposite end of the cavern.        A male tarantula drops down to block their escape. Sam BLOWS it away. Wade and Bret are still chipping away bits of gold.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Leave it!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: So you can keep it all!?   Hell no! Wade gets a nugget off the wall. He only has a nanosecond to admire it before Consuela suddenly looms behind him. (CONTINUED)
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: . CONTINUED:
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Dad! Bret reaches out toward his father. Wade reaches for him. Consuela's fangs suddenly protrude from Wade's chest and he's hauled backward. The tarantula flings Wade into the cave.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Bret, come on! Bret runs after the others. But he sees Consuela firing more quills at the group. Directly at Ashley. Bret leaps into harm's way. He's turned into a pin cushion.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Bret! Ashley goes to his side.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I'm sorry I... Bret dies.     Sam drags Ashley away from him. INT. MINES - NIGHT The survivors flee along the tunnel. Chris jumps up to rip down the string of light bulbs from the ceiling.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: We have to get out!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: This is our chance to kill them all. Chris smashes the bulb at the end of the strand.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: When the power comes on, the bulb will ignite the methane and torch them!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Where did you get an idea like that!? Chris looks at Gladys.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I blew up the kitchen. (CONTINUED)
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: . CONTINUED:
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Keep going up the tunnel. There should be a generator at the exit. Start it up and await for my signal to throw the switch.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: And the toxic waste...
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Will be buried under tons of rock! Go!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: What about you?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I need to set the fuse as close to the spiders as I can. That should give us time to get clear. Sam and Chris share a brief beat. And then Chris pulls down the lights, dragging them back toward the tarantula's den.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: He has a cute butt.    Don't you think?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: .S.D.A. choice. INT. MINES - TARANTULA DEN - NIGHT Chris comes through with his light bulb fuse. Consuela and her babies are feasting on the bodies of Bret and Wade Hale. Chris finds a vent in the ground.       He sprinkles dust over it to identify a faint draft.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Bingo. He positions the shattered light bulb beside this gas jet. INT. MINE TUNNELS - NIGHT Mike helps Gladys up the tunnel. Sam and Ashley are behind. Suddenly a male tarantula steps out of the shadows, separating the groups. (CONTINUED)
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: . CONTINUED:
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Mom!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Keep going! Sam and Ashley flee down another tunnel. INT. MINES - TARANTULA DEN - NIGHT Chris finishes preparing the booby trap. He gets up to leave. Only to find Consuela coming toward him.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I hate spiders. Chris runs out of the cavern. INT. MINE TUNNEL - NIGHT Chris bails out of the cavern and starts running. INT. MINE TUNNELS - NIGHT Sam and Ashley flee the male tarantula. Sam stumbles over something on the ground. It's Bret Hale's lost motorcycle. Ashley looks back and sees the tarantula coming after them.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Hurry! Sam lifts the MOTORCYCLE upright and climbs on. She STARTS it and REVS the ENGINE. Ashley leaps aboard. Sam accelerates along the shaft, away from the spider. The bike's headlight illuminates their path. The male tarantula scurries after the bike. Sam rides the motorcycle along the shaft. Ashley hangs on tight. They've put some distance between themselves and the male tarantula. A dead-end looms before them. Ashley screams as her mom stops on a dime and does a 180. Sam rides back the way they came, heading straight toward the male tarantula. Ashley looks over her mother's shoulder at the giant spider coming in the opposite direction.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Oh shit. (CONTINUED)
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: . CONTINUED: Sam lifts the bike into a wheelie as the tarantula nears.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Banzai! With perfect timing, she brings the front wheel down hard onto the tarantula's back. Crunch! The spider is roadkill. Sam steers them down another tunnel. EXT. MINE TUNNEL EXIT - NEAR WADE'S RANCH - DAWN Mike and Gladys gather at a generator just shy of the tunnel exit. Mike tries to start the generator. It won't catch.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: It needs gas!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: There's a ranch! Gladys heads over toward Wade's ranch. INT. MINE TUNNEL - DAWN Chris runs along the tunnel. Consuela charges after him, Chris reaches up, smashing more light bulbs as he runs. EXT. MINE TUNNEL EXIT - NEAR WADE'S RANCH - DAWN Mike is at the generator as Sam and Ashley ride up on the motorcycle.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: It needs gas! Sam tips over the motorcycle, trying to get gas out of the tank. It's clear this is not going to work.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Hurry! INT. MINE TUNNEL - DAWN Chris runs.     Smashing light bulbs.   Consuela close behind.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Start the generator!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: . EXT. MINE TUNNEL EXIT - NEAR WADE'S RANCH - DAWN MIKE He's coming!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Hurry, Mom! Sam has dumped some fuel into the generator.   She tries to start it. It won't turn over. INT. MINE TUNNEL - DAWN Chris ducks as Consuela fires quills at him.   He keeps going. INT. MINE TUNNEL EXIT - DAWN Sam sees Chris at the bottom of the tunnel. She tries to start the generator again but it refuses to cooperate.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Throw the switch!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I don't have any power!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Yo, Mom! Sam turns as Ashley throws her the STUN GUN. Sam catches it and brings it down to the light bulb cable... ZAPPING it. INT. MINE TUNNEL - DAWN As Chris runs, the light bulbs illuminate sequentially, traveling past him into the cavern. INT. MINE TUNNEL - DAWN A broken light bulb sparks. The filament ignites the gas-filled tunnel. A ball of flame spreads throughout the mines. INT. MINES - TARANTULA DEN - DAWN A huge column of flame blasts into the chamber. All the gold is illuminated. Consuela's babies are burned like popcorn.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: . EXT. MINE TUNNEL EXIT - NEAR WADE'S RANCH - DAY Sam looks back to see Chris running toward her. Consuela is on his heels. The glow of a fireball is right behind them.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Come on! Chris looks over his shoulder at Consuela and the flames.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Chris! Chris makes it to Sam just ahead of the conflagration. EXT. DESERT - NEAR WADE'S RANCH - DAY Sam and Chris dive out of the mine opening. A pillar of flame shoots out behind them.   Ashley and Mike are nearby. The town is visible just a mile away. EXT. TOWN - DAY The spiders retreat from daylight. Scuttling back into the buildings. Heading down into the mine shafts. INT. VARIOUS MINE TUNNELS - DAY The chain reaction spreads through the mines.      Jets of flame blast up tunnels. Torching any unlucky spiders looking for a home. Rupturing the very earth around them. EXT. DESERT - NEAR WADE'S RANCH - DAY The EARTH BEGINS TO SHAKE VIOLENTLY.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Earthquake!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: No! It's a chain reaction! The whole valley is going to blow!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: We'll never get out in time! Gladys drives up in     Wade's humvee.   Cigar in mouth. (CONTINUED)
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: . CONTINUED:
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Let's get the fuck out of here! The survivors pile into the truck as the town begins to BLOW UP in the distance. Chris is just about to climb aboard when... A webline shoots out of the nearby mine shaft. Consuela lives! The spider is charred and bloody. But she's primed for revenge. Chris is yanked off his feet and hauled toward her.            He fumbles for his machete and hacks at the webline. Cutting himself free just before getting impaled on Consuela's fangs. Consuela knocks away Chris's machete and lunges down at him. Chris kicks her belly with both his feet. Consuela begins to shudder. Jagged cracks appear in her charred carapace. Chris kicks and tears at the failing armor. He thinks he's harming the tarantula, but he's actually helping it! Mike and the others watch from the humvee.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Oh no... she's molting! Consuela's blistered shell cracks as she shrugs the damaged skin away from her body. Chris is amazed to see the spider has grown a full size larger and become totally rejuvenated! Consuela comes after Chris.        He defends himself with the machete. Shining steel makes contact with the dripping fangs. Once again Consuela punts away the machete. She prepares the death blow. It looks like curtains for Chris.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Consuela!   No!     Bad!   Bad Consuela! The massive spider stops in shock.            Chris looks back to see Mike has returned. TARANTULA POV The familiar multi-perspective spider vision.            The tarantula seems to recognize Mike.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: . BACK TO MIKE He throws his Cassiopeia PDA at the spider's face... Chris uses this moment of confusion to grab his machete and drive it deep into the spider's unprotected abdomen... The tarantula screams. Chris leaps up and runs, scooping up Mike.   They dive into the back of the humvee. Consuela tries to follow but is mortally wounded. She collapses in the dust. The TOWN EXPLODES in the b.g. The earth itself begins to collapse. INT. HUMVEE - DRIVING ACROSS DESERT - DAY Gladys accelerates as the town sinks in the distance. BUILDINGS EXPLODE. Jets of flame burst upward. The mall is sucked into the widening pit of collapsing earth. The humvee is just a cart length ahead of a wave of crumbling desert. EXT. HIGHWAY - DAY The humvee reaches open road. The survivors watch out the back as Prosperity disappears into a massive sinkhole. EXT. HIGHWAY/INT. HUMVEE - MOVING - DAY The group sits in a long beat of abject shock. And then Chris looks down to see his tight pants have finally ripped.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I really need some pants that fit. The group smiles.    Happy to be alive.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Look out! Everyone looks to the road ahead. A familiar bunny rabbit hops across the highway. Gladys HONKS and swerves to avoid it. EXT. HIGHWAY - DAY The bunny gets clear as the humvee drives away toward safety. (CONTINUED)
direction.name: direction
